class Solution {
    public double myPow(double x, int n) {
        long binform=n;
        double ans=1;
        if(binform>0){
             while(binform>0){
            if(binform%2==1){
                ans=ans*x;
               
            }
             x=x*x;
                binform=binform/2;
        }

           return ans;

        }else{
            binform=-binform;
            while(binform>0){
            if(binform%2==1){
                ans=ans*x;
               
            }
             x=x*x;
                binform=binform/2;
        }
        return 1/ans;
        }
       
        
    }
}

Why it's optimal
Time Complexity: O(log n) ✅
You divide n by 2 in every iteration.
Space Complexity: O(1) ✅
Only a few variables are used.
